With any version of conda newer than 4.1, using both bash and zsh I see `/foo/bin` dropped from PATH in the last echo statement.  

Before 4.1, `activate` would reorder PATH, putting the latest activated environment at the beginning of PATH but any modifications between the first and second activate would at least still be there.  I was willing to live with that behavior because the help for activate clearly documented that it put the new environment first.

Is this new(er) behavior intentional?

